<h3>Question 3</h3>
<div><p><p>Under what conditions Binomial distribution tends to Poisson distribution? The number of telephone calls received during the month of May is summarized in the following table.</p>
<div class="table_wrapper"><table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Number of telephone calls per day</td>
<td>0</td>
<td>1</td>
<td>2</td>
<td>3</td>
<td>4</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Number of days</td>
<td>8</td>
<td>12</td>
<td>18</td>
<td>13</td>
<td>9</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Fit the Poisson distribution.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>The Binomial distribution tends to the Poisson distribution under the following conditions:</p>
<p>The number of trials in the Binomial distribution is very large (n → ∞).<br />
The probability of success in each trial (p) is very small (p → 0).<br />
The product of n and p remains constant (np = λ).<br />
Under these conditions, the Binomial distribution becomes increasingly difficult to compute, and the Poisson distribution provides a simpler and more convenient approximation.</p>
<p>The Poisson distribution is a limiting case of the Binomial distribution, where the number of trials becomes very large and the probability of success becomes very small, such that the expected number of successes remains constant. The Poisson distribution describes the probability of a given number of events occurring in a fixed interval of time, when the events occur independently and at a constant rate.</p>
<p>In practice, the Poisson distribution is often used as an approximation of the Binomial distribution in situations where the conditions above are satisfied, such as in rare events or in the analysis of large datasets. However, it is important to note that the Poisson distribution may not be an accurate approximation if these conditions are not met.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/q_3_11.jpg" alt="" width="1520" height="2200" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12842"></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/q_3_21.jpg" alt="" width="1700" height="1289" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-12843"></p>
</div>
